lass=&#34;line&#34;&gt;Order deny,allow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/Limit&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;Limit Cancel-Job CUPS-Authenticate-Job&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;AuthType Default&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;Require user @OWNER @SYSTEM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;Order deny,allow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/Limit&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;Limit All&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;Order deny,allow&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/Limit&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;/Policy&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;BrowseWebIF Yes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-4-Create-the-startup-script-usr-local-etc-rc-d-run-cups-sh-for-CUPS&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-4-Create-the-startup-script-usr-local-etc-rc-d-run-cups-sh-for-CUPS&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 4: Create the startup script (/usr/local/etc/rc.d/run_cups.sh) for CUPS&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 4: Create the startup script (/usr/local/etc/rc.d/run_cups.sh) for CUPS&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;12&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;13&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;14&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;15&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;16&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;#!/bin/sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt; # Allow time for devfs to initialize.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;sleep 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt; # This will allow LPT(parallel port) printers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;echo -e &amp;quot;[system=10] \nadd path &amp;apos;unlpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups\nadd path &amp;apos;ulpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups\nadd path &amp;apos;lpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups&amp;quot; &amp;gt; /etc/devfs.rules&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt; # Restart devfs so it can read new config.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;/etc/rc.d/devfs restart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt; # Allow time for devfs to initialize.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;sleep 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt; # Now let&amp;apos;s start CUPS!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;/usr/local/etc/rc.d/cupsd onestart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-5-Make-the-script-executable&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-5-Make-the-script-executable&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 5: Make the script executable&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 5: Make the script executable&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;`chmod 755 /usr/local/etc/rc.d/run_cups.sh`&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-6-Add-rule-to-devfs-so-CUPS-print-server-can-start-on-boot&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-6-Add-rule-to-devfs-so-CUPS-print-server-can-start-on-boot&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 6: Add rule to devfs so CUPS print server can start on boot&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 6: Add rule to devfs so CUPS print server can start on boot&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add two lines to /etc/rc.conf&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;cupsd_enable=&amp;quot;YES&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;devfs_system_ruleset=&amp;quot;system&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;Step-7-Disable-CUPS-during-reboot-and-shutdown&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Step-7-Disable-CUPS-during-reboot-and-shutdown&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Step 7: Disable CUPS during reboot and shutdown&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Step 7: Disable CUPS during reboot and shutdown&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Add the following command to &amp;#x201C;/etc/rc.reboot&amp;#x201D; and &amp;#x201C;/etc/rc.shutdown&amp;#x201D; before the line that says &amp;#x201C;# If PLATFORM is pfSense then remove&amp;#x201D;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;/usr/local/etc/rc.d/cupsd stop&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;All set. Start CUPS now&lt;/strong&gt; Reboot or use command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;/usr/local/etc/rc.d/run_cups.sh&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Add printer to CUPS:&lt;/strong&gt; Now open up your web browser and go to &amp;#x201C;&lt;a href=&#34;http://your/&#34;&gt;http://Your&lt;/a&gt; pfSense address:631&amp;#x201D;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;Printer-driver&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Printer-driver&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Printer driver:&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Printer driver:&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foomatic&lt;/strong&gt;: a database-driven system for integrating free software printer drivers with common spoolers under Unix. If you receive error &amp;#x201C;stopped with status 22&amp;#x201D;. Install foomatic-db + dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;pkg_add -r foomatic-db foomatic-filters&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;hplip&lt;/strong&gt;: HP drivers for DeskJet, OfficeJet, Photosmart, Business Inkjet and some LaserJet printer models, as well as a number of Brother printers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;pkg_add -r hplip&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;gutenprint&lt;/strong&gt;: A collection of high quality drivers for Canon, Epson, Lexmark, Sony, Olympus, and PCL printers for use with GhostScript, CUPS, Foomatic, and the GIMP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;pkg_add -r  gutenprint&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;splix&lt;/strong&gt;: Samsung drivers for SPL (Samsung Printer Language) printers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;pkg_add -r  splix&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&#34;Missing-printer-driver-file-PPD&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;#Missing-printer-driver-file-PPD&#34; class=&#34;headerlink&#34; title=&#34;Missing printer driver file PPD?&#34;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Missing printer driver file PPD?&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Some printers&amp;#x2019; PPD are available in &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.openprinting.org/printers&#34;&gt;http://www.openprinting.org/printers&lt;/a&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Troubleshooting:&lt;/strong&gt; If you receive error: &amp;#x201C;Unable to create certificate file /var/run/cups/certs/0 - No such file or directory&amp;#x201D;, add the following command to the startup script.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;mkdir -r /var/run/cups/certs/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you receive error: &amp;#x201C;cupsdReadClient: Unable to write 14 bytes to /var/spool/cups/00000005: Bad file descriptor&amp;#x201D;, add the following command to the startup script.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;mkdir -pv /var/spool/cups/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If your CUPS decided to detect printers as a /dev/ulpt1 /dev/ulpt0 instead of the correctly detected printer (with /dev/usb/0.2.* and /dev/usb/0.3.*), to enable printing with local printer you need to give group &amp;#x2018;cups&amp;#x2019; r/w access to printer device: 1) Add following to /etc/devfs.rules (create if it doesn&amp;#x2019;t exist):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;[system=10]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;add path &amp;apos;unlpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;add path &amp;apos;ulpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;add path &amp;apos;lpt*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;And following to /etc/rc.conf:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;devfs_system_ruleset=&amp;quot;system&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Restart devfs:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;/etc/rc.d/devfs restart&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If your system supports &amp;#x2018;devd&amp;#x2019; you can copy $PREFIX/share/examples/cups/lpt-cupsd.conf to $PREFIX/etc/devd/ To enable printing under Gimp and MS-Windows clients do the following:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Uncomment application/octet-stream line in mime.types&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Uncomment application/octet-stream line in mime.convs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt; Restart cupsd&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are using libusb, it is important that no device driver, e.g. ulpt(4) is attached to the device you wish to use. In this case please ensure the cups user and group has read/write access to /dev/ugen* If you are using a USB printer wtih FreeBSD 8.0 or later, you will need to find the proper /dev/usb/* device pointed at by the /dev/ugen* entry. Follow the instructions for devfs.rules as above, but append a rule similar to the following for a printer attached as /dev/ugen0.2:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;figure class=&#34;highlight plain hljs&#34;&gt;&lt;table&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;gutter&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;code&#34;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;add path &amp;apos;usb/0.2.*&amp;apos; mode 0660 group cups&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content>
